---
import { getEntry } from "astro:content";
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { Scrollytelling } from "../components/Scrollytelling";
import { OutroComparison } from "../components/OutroComparison";
import { scenes } from "../content/posts/just-run-a-migration/scenes";

// Pulls title/description/etc from the content-collection stub so the
// homepage card, RSS feed, and this page's <head> stay in sync.
const entry = await getEntry("blog", "just-run-a-migration");
if (!entry) throw new Error("blog/just-run-a-migration entry missing");

// Reading-time estimate. Strip code fences (which inflate word count
// disproportionately to actual reading), then count whitespace-delimited
// tokens across all prose. 220 wpm is a typical read speed for technical
// blog content.
const allProse = scenes.map((s) => s.prose).join("\n");
const wordsOnly = allProse.replace(/```[\s\S]*?```/g, "").replace(/`[^`]*`/g, "");
const wordCount = wordsOnly.split(/\s+/).filter(Boolean).length;
const readMinutes = Math.max(1, Math.round(wordCount / 220));

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, "");
---

<BaseLayout title={entry.data.title} description={entry.data.description}>
	<main>
		<p class="post-back">
			<a href={`${base}/`}>&larr; all posts</a>
		</p>

		<section class="intro" data-pagefind-body>
			<h1>From <code>ALTER TABLE</code> to automated DB rollout</h1>
			<p class="subtitle">
				anatomy of a modern database migration
			</p>
			<p class="meta">~{readMinutes} min read</p>
			<p>
				<code>ALTER TABLE widgets ADD COLUMN color;</code> - as simple as you can get.
				In an automated pipeline though, that one statement passes through
				SQLAlchemy, Alembic, Docker, Kubernetes, Helm, GitHub Actions,
				ArgoCD, and Terraform before the new column actually exists in
				prod.
			</p>
			<p>
				None of that stack dropped from the sky. Each piece showed up to
				solve a real problem the previous setup couldn&rsquo;t handle.
				Here&rsquo;s the walkthrough, one layer at a time.
			</p>
			<p><em>Scroll to begin.</em></p>
		</section>

		<Scrollytelling client:load scenes={scenes} />

		<section class="outro">
			<h2>So, what&rsquo;s a migration, today?</h2>
			<p>
				For an engineer on the team, adding a column now looks like this:
				<ul>
				  <li>edit the SQLAlchemy model</li>
				<li>run <code>alembic revision --autogenerate</code></li>
				<li>open a PR</li>
				<li>merge</li>
			  </ul>
				Four steps, all in Python and git.
			</p>
			<p>
				Everything else in this post &mdash; the Dockerfiles, the
				Kubernetes Jobs and Deployments, the Helm hooks, the GitHub
				Actions checks, the ArgoCD Applications, the Terraform IAM
				roles &mdash; sits quietly underneath those four steps so they
				can stay that short.
			</p>
			<p>
				It&rsquo;s a lot of machinery for adding a single column. It&rsquo;s
				the right amount of machinery  when you need to be confident that
				changes will show up where they need, when they&rsquo;re needed,
				with testing and validation, without anyone having to remember anything.
			</p>

			<h3>Before and after</h3>
			<OutroComparison />
		</section>

		<footer class="tools">
			<h3>Tools mentioned</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>
					<a href="https://www.sqlalchemy.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">SQLAlchemy</a> &mdash;
					Python ORM and DDL generator.
				</li>
				<li>
					<a href="https://alembic.sqlalchemy.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Alembic</a> &mdash;
					schema migrations on top of SQLAlchemy.
				</li>
				<li>
					<a href="https://docs.docker.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Docker</a> &mdash;
					containerizes the app and the migration runner.
				</li>
				<li>
					<a href="https://kubernetes.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Kubernetes</a> &mdash;
					orchestrates Deployments and Jobs.
				</li>
				<li>
					<a href="https://helm.sh/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Helm</a> &mdash;
					templated, versioned k8s manifests.
				</li>
				<li>
					<a href="https://docs.github.com/en/actions" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub Actions</a> &mdash;
					CI: builds images and runs <code>alembic check</code> on PRs.
				</li>
				<li>
					<a href="https://argo-cd.readthedocs.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ArgoCD</a> &mdash;
					GitOps controller for k8s.
				</li>
				<li>
					<a href="https://www.terraform.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Terraform</a> &mdash;
					infrastructure as code for AWS resources.
				</li>
				<li>
					<a href="https://docs.aws.amazon.com/eks/latest/userguide/iam-roles-for-service-accounts.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">IRSA</a> &mdash;
					IAM roles for Kubernetes service accounts (AWS OIDC federation).
				</li>
			</ul>
		</footer>
	</main>
</BaseLayout>
